whispApsMibModule.name: whispApsMibModule
whispApsMibModule.description: This module contains MIB definitions for APs.

gpsInput.name: gpsInput
gpsInput.description: The variable is deprecated. See gpsInput in whispBoxConfig.

rfFreqCarrier.name: rfFreqCarrier
rfFreqCarrier.description: The variable is deprecated. Please see radioFreqCarrier.

dwnLnkData.name: dwnLnkData
dwnLnkData.description: This attribute is deprecated. Please see radioDownlinkPercent.

highPriorityUpLnkPct.name: highPriorityUpLnkPct
highPriorityUpLnkPct.description: Percentage of uplink slots for high priority data.

numUAckSlots.name: numUAckSlots
numUAckSlots.description: Total number of upstream ack slots.

uAcksReservHigh.name: uAcksReservHigh
uAcksReservHigh.description: Total number of upstream high priority ack slots

numDAckSlots.name: numDAckSlots
numDAckSlots.description: Total number of downstream ack slots.

dAcksReservHigh.name: dAcksReservHigh
dAcksReservHigh.description: Total number of high priority downstream ack slots.

numCtlSlots.name: numCtlSlots
numCtlSlots.description: This OID is deprecated, please use numCtlSlotsHW.

numCtlSlotsReserveHigh.name: numCtlSlotsReserveHigh
numCtlSlotsReserveHigh.description: Total number of High priority upstream control (contention) slots.

sectorID.name: sectorID
sectorID.description: Advertise sector number for an AP. Not supported for PMP450.

maxRange.name: maxRange
maxRange.description: This attribute is deprecated. Please see radioMaxRange.

airLinkSecurity.name: airLinkSecurity
airLinkSecurity.description: Air Link Security. desEnhancedAndAuthentication(2) and authenticationIfAvailable(3) are only for APAS.

gpsTrap.name: gpsTrap
gpsTrap.description: Variable to enable/disable GPS sync/out-sync traps.

regTrap.name: regTrap
regTrap.description: Variable to enable/disable registration complete/lost traps.

txSpreading.name: txSpreading
txSpreading.description: Variable to enable/disable Transmit Frame Spreading. This option is for FSK only.

apBeaconInfo.name: apBeaconInfo
apBeaconInfo.description: Variable to enable/disable displaying AP beacon info through AP eval.

authMode.name: authMode
authMode.description: Variable to enable/disable authentication. The authentication optional mode is for APs only. This variable can only be set when authentication feature is enabled. Setting it to 1 will use a BAM server for authentication of SMs. Setting it to 2 will make use of the Authentication Key on the AP for authenticating SMs. The keys must match on SM and AP in order for the SM to be authenticated in this mode.

authKeyAp.name: authKeyAp
authKeyAp.description: Authentication key. It should be 32 character long. Can be used on MultiPoint AP if AP Authentication mode is selected. Otherwise, it is used on Backhauls.

ntpServerIp.name: ntpServerIp
ntpServerIp.description: Obsoleted. Configure with whispApsDNS.ntpServer1, whispApsDNS.ntpServer2, and whispApsDNS.ntpServer3.

broadcastRetryCount.name: broadcastRetryCount
broadcastRetryCount.description: Broadcast Repeat Count : Range 0 -- 2. For APs.

encryptDwBroadcast.name: encryptDwBroadcast
encryptDwBroadcast.description: To enable or disable Encrypted Downlink Broadcast. For FSK APs.

dfsConfig.name: dfsConfig
dfsConfig.description: To configure proper regions for Dynamic Frequency Shifting. For 5.2/5.4/5.7 GHz radios.

configSource.name: configSource
configSource.description: To configure CIR, MIR and VLAN through SM or BAM.

apRateAdapt.name: apRateAdapt
apRateAdapt.description: To enable or disable double rate.

numCtlSlotsHW.name: numCtlSlotsHW
numCtlSlotsHW.description: This attribute is deprecated. Please see radioControlSlots.

displayAPEval.name: displayAPEval
displayAPEval.description: If enable, it allows display of AP Eval Data at the SM.

smIsolation.name: smIsolation
smIsolation.description: (0) -- Disable SM Isolation. (1) -- Enable SM Isolation by blocking SM destined packets. (2) -- Enable SM Isolation by forwarding SM packets upstream.

ipAccessFilterEnable.name: ipAccessFilterEnable
ipAccessFilterEnable.description: To enable or disable IP access filtering to Management functions. (0) - IP access will be allowed from all addresses. (1) - IP access will be controlled using allowedIPAccess1-3 entries.

allowedIPAccess1.name: allowedIPAccess1
allowedIPAccess1.description: Allow access to AP Management from this IP. 0 is default setting to allow from all IPs.

allowedIPAccess2.name: allowedIPAccess2
allowedIPAccess2.description: Allow access to AP Management from this IP. 0 is default setting to allow from all IPs.

allowedIPAccess3.name: allowedIPAccess3
allowedIPAccess3.description: Allow access to AP Management from this IP. 0 is default setting to allow from all IPs.

tslBridging.name: tslBridging
tslBridging.description: 1 = We are performing Translation Bridging 0 = We are not.

untranslatedArp.name: untranslatedArp
untranslatedArp.description: 1 = We are sending untranslated ARP response. 0 = We are not.

limitFreqBand900.name: limitFreqBand900
limitFreqBand900.description: 1 = We are limiting the freq band of 900 radios. 0 = We are not.

scheduleWhitening.name: scheduleWhitening
scheduleWhitening.description: 1 = Schedule Whitening allowed. 0 = Schedule Whitening not allowed. This option is for FSK only

remoteSpectrumAnalysisDuration.name: remoteSpectrumAnalysisDuration
remoteSpectrumAnalysisDuration.description: Value in seconds for a remote spectrum analysis on an SM. Range is 10-1000 seconds.

remoteSpectrumAnalyzerLUID.name: remoteSpectrumAnalyzerLUID
remoteSpectrumAnalyzerLUID.description: Get will return always return 0. Set will start Remote Spectrum Analyzer on specified LUID. *Warning* This will cause the SM to disconnect from the AP! You will lose the session for the specified duration! If general error was returned then the LUID does not have an active session, or the SM does not support Remote Spectrum Analysis.

bhReReg.name: bhReReg
bhReReg.description: Allows BHS re-registration every 24 hours. Enable allows re-registration and Disable does not. 24 Hour Encryption Refresh.

verifyGPSChecksum.name: verifyGPSChecksum
verifyGPSChecksum.description: Enable/Disable verification of GPS message checksums.

apVlanOverride.name: apVlanOverride
apVlanOverride.description: Setting this option will cause an AP to retain its VLAN settings when turning it into an SM. It will be mostly helpful for running spectrum analysis on the AP. Since doing that requires the AP to be turned into an SM, enabling this option will allow you to keep the AP's VLAN configuration in place while the AP is running as an SM.

dhcpRelayAgentEnable.name: dhcpRelayAgentEnable
dhcpRelayAgentEnable.description: Enable or Disable MultiPoint AP acting as DHCP Relay Agent for all SMs and Clients underneath it. (0) - Relay Agent disabled - SM/CPE devices will perform DHCP normally (1) - Relay Agent enabled - AP will intercept DHCP DISCOVER message from SM and CPE, insert Option 82 containing SM's MAC address, and forward request to specified DHCP server.

colorCodeRescanTimer.name: colorCodeRescanTimer
colorCodeRescanTimer.description: Time in minutes for the subscriber to begin the idle timer. This timer will begin as soon as a session is started. This only fires if the device is in session with a non-primary color code. A value of zero (0) disables this timer (MultiPoint system Only)

colorCodeRescanIdleTimer.name: colorCodeRescanIdleTimer
colorCodeRescanIdleTimer.description: Time in minutes for the subscriber to check for an idle state. If an period has pass where no unicast RF traffic has occured (idle), then the subscriber will begin to rescan. This timer will wait until the timer set in colorCodeRescanTimer has expired before beginning. This timer only fires if the device is in session with a non-primary color code. A value of zero (0) mean to rescan without waiting for idle. (MultiPoint system Only)

authKeyOptionAP.name: authKeyOptionAP
authKeyOptionAP.description: This option is for Multipoint APs only. This option will only be used if Authentication Mode is set to AP Pre-Shared Key. 0 - Use default key. 1 - Use set key.

onlyAllowVer95OrAbove.name: onlyAllowVer95OrAbove
onlyAllowVer95OrAbove.description: Only allow subscribers that are running version 9.5 or above. Any radio that has a version below 9.5 will not be allowed to register.

apRxDelay.name: apRxDelay
apRxDelay.description: This is used for engineering debug and needs to be removed or moved to eng MIB before releasing the MIB.

qinqEthType.name: qinqEthType
qinqEthType.description: EtherType for QinQ (802.1ad) outer tag (S-Tag). 0x88a8 by default.

fskSMTxPwrCntl.name: fskSMTxPwrCntl
fskSMTxPwrCntl.description: Enable/Disable AP control of SM TX power. For FSK AP radios capable of Transmit Power Control.

fskSMRcvTargetLvl.name: fskSMRcvTargetLvl
fskSMRcvTargetLvl.description: Desired SM Receive Level at AP (dBm, Range -40dBm to -80 dBm).

dropSession.name: dropSession
dropSession.description: SM/BHS MAC Address to drop session from the AP/BHM.

uGPSPower.name: uGPSPower
uGPSPower.description: Enable or Disable power supply to Universal GPS module (UGPS capable APs only, when GPS_output_enable is NOT set).

ofdmSMRcvTargetLvl.name: ofdmSMRcvTargetLvl
ofdmSMRcvTargetLvl.description: Desired SM Receive Level at AP (dBm, Range -40dBm to -80 dBm). As of release 12.1, on MIMO systems this is a combined power level value.

radiusPort.name: radiusPort
radiusPort.description: Port used to connect to the RADIUS server. Default is 1812.

radiusAcctPort.name: radiusAcctPort
radiusAcctPort.description: Port used to for RADIUS Accounting. Default is 1813.

lastSesStatsReset.name: lastSesStatsReset
lastSesStatsReset.description: Displays the timestamp of last reset of session stats or None otherwise.

resetSesStats.name: resetSesStats
resetSesStats.description: Resets the session stats if true.

rfOLTrap.name: rfOLTrap
rfOLTrap.description: Enable/Disable SNMP Trap for when RF Overload exceeds configured Threshold level.

rfOLThreshold.name: rfOLThreshold
rfOLThreshold.description: Percent of packet overload in the RF Downlink where SNMP is generated and sent to Network Manager.

rfOLEnable.name: rfOLEnable
rfOLEnable.description: Enable/Disable Throughput RF Overload Monitoring monitoring.

actionListFilename.name: actionListFilename
actionListFilename.description: Name of the file that contains the Action List for Auto update commands from CNUT

enableAutoupdate.name: enableAutoupdate
enableAutoupdate.description: Enables/Disables auto-update of the SM's under an AP

accountingSmReAuthInterval.name: accountingSmReAuthInterval
accountingSmReAuthInterval.description: Select Interval for Reauthentication of SM

syslogDomainNameAppend.name: syslogDomainNameAppend
syslogDomainNameAppend.description: This attribute is deprecated. Use syslogDomainNameAppend in whispBoxAttributesGroup

syslogServerAddr.name: syslogServerAddr
syslogServerAddr.description: This attribute is deprecated. Use syslogServerAddr in whispBoxAttributesGroup

syslogServerPort.name: syslogServerPort
syslogServerPort.description: This attribute is deprecated. Use syslogServerPort in whispBoxAttributesGroup

syslogXmitAP.name: syslogXmitAP
syslogXmitAP.description: Enables/Disables transmission of Syslogs from AP/BHM

syslogXmitSMs.name: syslogXmitSMs
syslogXmitSMs.description: Enables/Disables transmission of Syslogs from connected SMs/BHS. This can be over-ridden by the setting on individual SMs/ the BHS.

gpsOutputEn.name: gpsOutputEn
gpsOutputEn.description: Enable or Disable GPS sync output enable.

rfPPPoEPADIForwarding.name: rfPPPoEPADIForwarding
rfPPPoEPADIForwarding.description: Enables/disables forwarding of PPPoE PADI packets from AP to SM.

allowedIPAccessNMLength1.name: allowedIPAccessNMLength1
allowedIPAccessNMLength1.description: Length of the network mask to apply to the AllowedIPAddress when assessing if access is allowed

allowedIPAccessNMLength2.name: allowedIPAccessNMLength2
allowedIPAccessNMLength2.description: Length of the network mask to apply to the AllowedIPAddress when assessing if access is allowed

allowedIPAccessNMLength3.name: allowedIPAccessNMLength3
allowedIPAccessNMLength3.description: Length of the network mask to apply to the AllowedIPAddress when assessing if access is allowed

bridgeFloodUnknownsEnable.name: bridgeFloodUnknownsEnable
bridgeFloodUnknownsEnable.description: To enable or disable bridge flooding unknown unicast packets. (0) - Bridge will not forward unknown unicast packets. (1) - Bridge will flood unknown unicast packets.

berModSelect.name: berModSelect
berModSelect.description: The modulation the AP generates BER at. 0 for QPSK, 1 for 16-QAM, 2 for 64-QAM, and 3 for 256-QAM.

remoteSpectrumAnalyzerScanBandwidth.name: remoteSpectrumAnalyzerScanBandwidth
remoteSpectrumAnalyzerScanBandwidth.description: Scanning Bandwidth used for the Remote Spectrum Analyzer. Only available on PMP 450.

multicastVCDataRate.name: multicastVCDataRate
multicastVCDataRate.description: The data rate that is used for the Multicast VC. 8X is for engineering only.

multicastRetryCount.name: multicastRetryCount
multicastRetryCount.description: Multicast Repeat Count : Range 0 - 2. For APs.

apConfigAdjacentChanSupport.name: apConfigAdjacentChanSupport
apConfigAdjacentChanSupport.description: Used to enable or disable adjacent channel support.

whispRegStatus.name: whispRegStatus
whispRegStatus.description: This shows the registration status of a link.

linkTestLUID.name: linkTestLUID
linkTestLUID.description: LUID selection for Link Test. Valid range: 2-255

linkTestDuration.name: linkTestDuration
linkTestDuration.description: Duration for the Link Test. Valid range: 2-10 seconds

linkTestAction.name: linkTestAction
linkTestAction.description: Setting value 1 will initiate link test. Note that trying to set 0 will not stop the test. In fact it will return an error message. The value of 0 just indicates the idle state meaning no test is running or the current test is done. That's why the word stopped is used and not the action verb stop.

linkTestPktLength.name: linkTestPktLength
linkTestPktLength.description: Packet length for Link Test. Valid range: 64-1714 bytes

linkTestMode.name: linkTestMode
linkTestMode.description: Link Test Mode 0 = RF Link Test (traffic doesn't go through bridge, highest throughput) 1 = Link Test with Bridging 2 = Link Test with Bridging and MIR

linkTestSNRCalculation.name: linkTestSNRCalculation
linkTestSNRCalculation.description: Enable or disable Signal to Noise Ratio (SNR) calculations during a Link Test. Enabling(1) will calulate SNR on all receiving packets. Due to load on CPU, will slightly degrade packet per second capabilities. Only applicable to GenII OFDM products and up.

linkTestWithDualPath.name: linkTestWithDualPath
linkTestWithDualPath.description: Link Test with: 0 = Low Priority VC only 1 = High and Low Priority VCs

linkTestNumPkt.name: linkTestNumPkt
linkTestNumPkt.description: Number of packets to send. Valid range: 0-64 where 0 will flood the link for the duration of the test.

linkTestError.name: linkTestError
linkTestError.description: Error status of Link Test: (1) Failed to recieve handshake from remote device (2) No session is currently active. Please try again after session established. (3) Received a bad transaction ID. Please try again. (4) We werent able to send the test request to the remote device. (5) We didnt receive any results from the remote device.

maxDwnLinkIndex.name: maxDwnLinkIndex
maxDwnLinkIndex.description: For link test results, the maximum possible downlink efficiency percentage (always 100%).

maxUpLinkIndex.name: maxUpLinkIndex
maxUpLinkIndex.description: For link test results, the maximum possible uplink efficiency percentage (always 100%).

fragments1xDwnLinkVertical.name: fragments1xDwnLinkVertical
fragments1xDwnLinkVertical.description: Number of fragments received on down link at 1X (QPSK). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

fragments2xDwnLinkVertical.name: fragments2xDwnLinkVertical
fragments2xDwnLinkVertical.description: Number of fragments received on down link at 2X (16-QAM). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

fragments3xDwnLinkVertical.name: fragments3xDwnLinkVertical
fragments3xDwnLinkVertical.description: Number of fragments received on down link at 3X (64-QAM). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

fragments4xDwnLinkVertical.name: fragments4xDwnLinkVertical
fragments4xDwnLinkVertical.description: Number of fragments received on down link at 4X (256-QAM). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

fragments1xUpLinkVertical.name: fragments1xUpLinkVertical
fragments1xUpLinkVertical.description: Number of fragments received on up link at 1X (QPSK). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

fragments2xUpLinkVertical.name: fragments2xUpLinkVertical
fragments2xUpLinkVertical.description: Number of fragments received on up link at 2X (16-QAM). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

fragments3xUpLinkVertical.name: fragments3xUpLinkVertical
fragments3xUpLinkVertical.description: Number of fragments received on up link at 3X (64-QAM). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

fragments4xUpLinkVertical.name: fragments4xUpLinkVertical
fragments4xUpLinkVertical.description: Number of fragments received on up link at 4X (256-QAM). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

bitErrorsCorrected1xDwnLinkVertical.name: bitErrorsCorrected1xDwnLinkVertical
bitErrorsCorrected1xDwnLinkVertical.description: Number of bit errors corrected on average per fragment on down link at 1X (QPSK). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

bitErrorsCorrected2xDwnLinkVertical.name: bitErrorsCorrected2xDwnLinkVertical
bitErrorsCorrected2xDwnLinkVertical.description: Number of bit errors corrected on average per fragment on down link at 2X (16-QAM). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

bitErrorsCorrected3xDwnLinkVertical.name: bitErrorsCorrected3xDwnLinkVertical
bitErrorsCorrected3xDwnLinkVertical.description: Number of bit errors corrected on average per fragment on down link at 3X (64-QAM). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

bitErrorsCorrected4xDwnLinkVertical.name: bitErrorsCorrected4xDwnLinkVertical
bitErrorsCorrected4xDwnLinkVertical.description: Number of bit errors corrected on average per fragment on down link at 4X (256-QAM). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

bitErrorsCorrected1xUpLinkVertical.name: bitErrorsCorrected1xUpLinkVertical
bitErrorsCorrected1xUpLinkVertical.description: Number of bit errors corrected on average per fragment on up link at 1X (QPSK). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

bitErrorsCorrected2xUpLinkVertical.name: bitErrorsCorrected2xUpLinkVertical
bitErrorsCorrected2xUpLinkVertical.description: Number of bit errors corrected on average per fragment on up link at 2X (16-QAM). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

bitErrorsCorrected3xUpLinkVertical.name: bitErrorsCorrected3xUpLinkVertical
bitErrorsCorrected3xUpLinkVertical.description: Number of bit errors corrected on average per fragment on up link at 3X (64-QAM). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

bitErrorsCorrected4xUpLinkVertical.name: bitErrorsCorrected4xUpLinkVertical
bitErrorsCorrected4xUpLinkVertical.description: Number of bit errors corrected on average per fragment on up link at 4X (256-QAM). For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

signalToNoiseRatioDownLinkVertical.name: signalToNoiseRatioDownLinkVertical
signalToNoiseRatioDownLinkVertical.description: Estimated Signal to Noise Ratio in dB for the down link. For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

signalToNoiseRatioUpLinkVertical.name: signalToNoiseRatioUpLinkVertical
signalToNoiseRatioUpLinkVertical.description: Estimated Signal to Noise Ratio in dB for the up link. For Gen II OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

fragments1xDwnLinkHorizontal.name: fragments1xDwnLinkHorizontal
fragments1xDwnLinkHorizontal.description: Number of fragments received on down link at 1X (QPSK). For MIMO only. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

fragments2xDwnLinkHorizontal.name: fragments2xDwnLinkHorizontal
fragments2xDwnLinkHorizontal.description: Number of fragments received on down link at 2X (16-QAM). For MIMO only. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

fragments3xDwnLinkHorizontal.name: fragments3xDwnLinkHorizontal
fragments3xDwnLinkHorizontal.description: Number of fragments received on down link at 3X (64-QAM). For MIMO only. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

fragments4xDwnLinkHorizontal.name: fragments4xDwnLinkHorizontal
fragments4xDwnLinkHorizontal.description: Number of fragments received on down link at 4X (256-QAM). For MIMO only. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

fragments1xUpLinkHorizontal.name: fragments1xUpLinkHorizontal
fragments1xUpLinkHorizontal.description: Number of fragments received on up link at 1X (QPSK). For MIMO only. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

fragments2xUpLinkHorizontal.name: fragments2xUpLinkHorizontal
fragments2xUpLinkHorizontal.description: Number of fragments received on up link at 2X (16-QAM). For MIMO only. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

fragments3xUpLinkHorizontal.name: fragments3xUpLinkHorizontal
fragments3xUpLinkHorizontal.description: Number of fragments received on up link at 3X (64-QAM). For MIMO only. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

fragments4xUpLinkHorizontal.name: fragments4xUpLinkHorizontal
fragments4xUpLinkHorizontal.description: Number of fragments received on up link at 4X (256-QAM). For MIMO only. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

bitErrorsCorrected1xDwnLinkHorizontal.name: bitErrorsCorrected1xDwnLinkHorizontal
bitErrorsCorrected1xDwnLinkHorizontal.description: Number of bit errors corrected on average per fragment on down link at 1X (QPSK). For MIMO and forward. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

bitErrorsCorrected2xUpLinkHorizontal.name: bitErrorsCorrected2xUpLinkHorizontal
bitErrorsCorrected2xUpLinkHorizontal.description: Number of bit errors corrected on average per fragment on up link at 2X (16-QAM). For MIMO and forward. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

bitErrorsCorrected3xUpLinkHorizontal.name: bitErrorsCorrected3xUpLinkHorizontal

bitErrorsCorrected4xUpLinkHorizontal.name: bitErrorsCorrected4xUpLinkHorizontal
bitErrorsCorrected4xUpLinkHorizontal.description: Number of bit errors corrected on average per fragment on up link at 4X (256-QAM). For MIMO and forward. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

ntpDomainNameAppend.description: Select whether to append the configured management domain name to the configured trap names. For example, if dnsMgmtDomainName is set to 'example.com', ntpServer is set to 'ntp', and ntpDomainNameAppend is set to appendDomain, the ntpServer name used would be 'ntp.example.com'.

ntpServer1.description: NTP Server 1 Address. Format is either an IP address or DNS name.

ntpServer3.description: NTP Server 3 Address. Format is either an IP address or DNS name.

dhcprDomainNameAppend.name: dhcprDomainNameAppend
dhcprDomainNameAppend.description: Select whether to append the configured management domain name to the configured trap names. For example, if dnsMgmtDomainName is set to 'example.com', dhcprServer is set to 'dhcpr', and dhcprDomainNameAppend is set to appendDomain, the dhcprServer name used would be 'dhcpr.example.com'.

dhcprServer.description: DHCP Server IP which will be used for forwarding DHCP messages by the DHCP Relay Agent in the MultiPoint AP. - Format is either an IP address or DNS name. - Default is 255.255.255.255 (broadcast).

authDomainNameAppend.description: Select whether to append the configured management domain name to the configured trap names. For example, if dnsMgmtDomainName is set to 'example.com', authServer1 is set to 'auth1', and authDomainNameAppend is set to appendDomain, the authServer1 name used would be 'auth1.example.com'.

authServer1.description: Authentication Server 1. Format is either an IP address or DNS name.

clearLinkTableStats.name: clearLinkTableStats
clearLinkTableStats.description: Setting this to a nonzero value will clear the link table stats.

radioFreqCarrier.name: radioFreqCarrier
radioFreqCarrier.description: RF Frequency. Please see the whispBoxRFPhysicalRadioFrequencies SNMP table for a list of available frequencies. 0: wired.

radioDownlinkPercent.name: radioDownlinkPercent
radioDownlinkPercent.description: This is the percentage of frame data space allocated for downlink.

radioControlSlots.name: radioControlSlots
radioControlSlots.description: Total number of control slots for HW Scheduling Point-to-Mulitpoint mode (Not applicable for PtoP radios). For PMP450 the minimum is 1 control slot, others minimum is zero. Maximum control slots is 15.

linkDescr.name: linkDescr
linkDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the unit. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the hardware interface.

linkMtu.name: linkMtu
linkMtu.description: The size of the largest datagram which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets. For interfaces that are used for transmitting network datagrams, this is the size of the largest network datagram that can be sent on the interface.

linkSpeed.name: linkSpeed
linkSpeed.description: An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in bits per second. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth.

linkInOctets.name: linkInOctets
linkInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters.

linkInUcastPkts.name: linkInUcastPkts
linkInUcastPkts.description: The number of subnetwork-unicast packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

linkInNUcastPkts.name: linkInNUcastPkts
linkInNUcastPkts.description: The number of non-unicast (i.e., subnetwork- broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

linkInDiscards.name: linkInDiscards
linkInDiscards.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

linkInError.name: linkInError
linkInError.description: The number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

linkInUnknownProtos.name: linkInUnknownProtos
linkInUnknownProtos.description: The number of packets received via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

linkOutOctets.name: linkOutOctets
linkOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters.

linkOutUcastPkts.name: linkOutUcastPkts
linkOutUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a subnetwork-unicast address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

linkOutNUcastPkts.name: linkOutNUcastPkts
linkOutNUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non- unicast (i.e., a subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

linkOutDiscards.name: linkOutDiscards
linkOutDiscards.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

linkOutError.name: linkOutError
linkOutError.description: The number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors.

linkOutQLen.name: linkOutQLen
linkOutQLen.description: Number of packets in output packet queue.

linkSessState.name: linkSessState
linkSessState.description: Current operational state of an interface. 0 = Idle 1 = In Session 2 = Clearing 3 = Re-registration downlink reset 4 = Authentication Challenge 5 = Registering 6 = Not in use

linkESN.name: linkESN
linkESN.description: Link Electronic serial number. It is MAC address.

linkRSSI.name: linkRSSI
linkRSSI.description: The average RSSI reading of all packets received from an SM. Applicable to FSK radios only.

linkAveJitter.name: linkAveJitter
linkAveJitter.description: The average Jitter reading of all packets received from an SM. Applicable to FSK radios only.

linkLastJitter.name: linkLastJitter
linkLastJitter.description: Last jitter value. Applicable to FSK radios only.

linkAirDelay.name: linkAirDelay
linkAirDelay.description: The current round trip air delay in bits measured between the AP and SM.

linkRegCount.name: linkRegCount
linkRegCount.description: The number of times an SM has registered to an AP.

linkReRegCount.name: linkReRegCount
linkReRegCount.description: The number of times an SM has tried to register with the AP while it still has an active session with the AP.

linkLastRSSI.name: linkLastRSSI
linkLastRSSI.description: The last RSSI reading of all packets received from an SM. Applicable to FSK radios only.

sessionCount.name: sessionCount
sessionCount.description: How many times has this mac been in/out of session.

softwareVersion.name: softwareVersion
softwareVersion.description: The software version of registered SM.

softwareBootVersion.name: softwareBootVersion
softwareBootVersion.description: The software boot version of registered SM.

fpgaVersion.name: fpgaVersion
fpgaVersion.description: The FPGA version of registered SM.

linkSiteName.name: linkSiteName
linkSiteName.description: The site name of the registered SM.

avgPowerLevel.name: avgPowerLevel
avgPowerLevel.description: The average power level of registered SM. For systems that support power control, this value can read 'NA' when the AP adjusts the transmit power of a SM until new packets are received from the SM with it transmitting at its new power level. For MIMO this is the combined receive power.

lastPowerLevel.name: lastPowerLevel
lastPowerLevel.description: The last power level of registered SM. For MIMO radios this is the combined receive power.

smSessionSeqNumMismatch.name: smSessionSeqNumMismatch
smSessionSeqNumMismatch.description: The count of how many sequence number mismatch between the AP/BHM and the SM/BHS during the authentication challenge and authentication response messages. This status is only valid in a system where encryption is enabled and no authentication server is configured.

dataVCNum.name: dataVCNum
dataVCNum.description: The normal priority Data VC number in use for this link.

hiPriQEn.name: hiPriQEn
hiPriQEn.description: Returns whether High Priority channel is enabled. On P7/P8 devices will return 0 always. Use p7p8HiPriQEn OID for P7/P8 radios.

dataVCNumHiQ.name: dataVCNumHiQ
dataVCNumHiQ.description: The high priority Data VC number in use for this link, if any. If 0, no High Priority channel is in place.

linkInOctetsHiQ.name: linkInOctetsHiQ
linkInOctetsHiQ.description: The total number of octets received on High Priority Queue, including framing characters.

linkInUcastPktsHiQ.name: linkInUcastPktsHiQ
linkInUcastPktsHiQ.description: The number of subnetwork-unicast packets on High Priority Queue delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

linkInNUcastPktsHiQ.name: linkInNUcastPktsHiQ
linkInNUcastPktsHiQ.description: The number of non-unicast (i.e., subnetwork- broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) packets on High Priority Queue delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

linkInDiscardsHiQ.name: linkInDiscardsHiQ
linkInDiscardsHiQ.description: The number of inbound packets on High Priority Queue which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

linkInErrorHiQ.name: linkInErrorHiQ
linkInErrorHiQ.description: The number of inbound packets on High Priority Queue that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

linkInUnknownProtosHiQ.name: linkInUnknownProtosHiQ
linkInUnknownProtosHiQ.description: The number of packets received on High Priority Queue via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

linkOutOctetsHiQ.name: linkOutOctetsHiQ
linkOutOctetsHiQ.description: The total number of octets on High Priority Queue transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters.

linkOutUcastPktsHiQ.name: linkOutUcastPktsHiQ
linkOutUcastPktsHiQ.description: The total number of packets on High Priority Queue that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a subnetwork-unicast address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

linkOutNUcastPktsHiQ.name: linkOutNUcastPktsHiQ
linkOutNUcastPktsHiQ.description: The total number of packets on High Priority Queue that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non- unicast (i.e., a subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

linkOutDiscardsHiQ.name: linkOutDiscardsHiQ
linkOutDiscardsHiQ.description: The number of outbound packets on High Priority Queue which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

linkOutErrorHiQ.name: linkOutErrorHiQ
linkOutErrorHiQ.description: The number of outbound packets on High Priority Queue that could not be transmitted because of errors.

vcQOverflow.name: vcQOverflow
vcQOverflow.description: The number of packets dropped due to Queue overflow on VC.

vcQOverflowHiQ.name: vcQOverflowHiQ
vcQOverflowHiQ.description: The number of packets dropped due to Queue overflow on High Priority VC, if enabled.

p7p8HiPriQEn.name: p7p8HiPriQEn
p7p8HiPriQEn.description: Returns whether P7/P8 hi priority channel is enabled. On non-P7/P8 devices will return 0 always.

p7p8HiPriQ.name: p7p8HiPriQ
p7p8HiPriQ.description: Hi Priority Queue statistics for P7 or P8 radios, if enabled. If not enabled, or not a P7 or P8, will return 0.

linkAirDelayns.name: linkAirDelayns
linkAirDelayns.description: The current round trip air delay in nanoseconds measured between the AP and SM.

linkQualityAPData.name: linkQualityAPData
linkQualityAPData.description: The current link quality of the SM's data from the AP. This is relative to the current modulation rate (1X, 2X, 3X, etc).

linkManagementIP.description: Management IP Address of the unit. 0 indicates SM is not publically addressable.

linkFragmentsReceived1XVertical.name: linkFragmentsReceived1XVertical
linkFragmentsReceived1XVertical.description: Engineering use only. Number of fragments received in 1x (QPSK) modulation. For GenII OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

linkFragmentsReceived2XVertical.name: linkFragmentsReceived2XVertical
linkFragmentsReceived2XVertical.description: Engineering use only. Number of fragments received in 2x (16-QAM) modulation. For GenII OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

linkFragmentsReceived3XVertical.name: linkFragmentsReceived3XVertical
linkFragmentsReceived3XVertical.description: Engineering use only. Number of fragments received in 3x (64-QAM) modulation. For GenII OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

linkFragmentsReceived4XVertical.name: linkFragmentsReceived4XVertical
linkFragmentsReceived4XVertical.description: Engineering use only. Number of fragments received in 4x (256-QAM) modulation. For GenII OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

signalToNoiseRatioVertical.name: signalToNoiseRatioVertical
signalToNoiseRatioVertical.description: Estimate of the receive signal to noise ratio in dB. For GenII OFDM and forward. For MIMO this is the vertical path.

radiusReplyMsg.description: The RADIUS Reply-Msg populated for the SM. This is only valid when using a backen AAA server.

radiusFramedIPNetmask.name: radiusFramedIPNetmask
radiusFramedIPNetmask.description: This Attribute indicates the netmask to be configured for the SM management interface.

linkFragmentsReceived1XHorizontal.name: linkFragmentsReceived1XHorizontal
linkFragmentsReceived1XHorizontal.description: Engineering use only. Number of fragments received in 1x (QPSK) modulation. For MIMO only. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

linkFragmentsReceived2XHorizontal.name: linkFragmentsReceived2XHorizontal
linkFragmentsReceived2XHorizontal.description: Engineering use only. Number of fragments received in 2x (16-QAM) modulation. For MIMO only. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

linkFragmentsReceived3XHorizontal.name: linkFragmentsReceived3XHorizontal
linkFragmentsReceived3XHorizontal.description: Engineering use only. Number of fragments received in 3x (64-QAM) modulation. For MIMO only. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

linkFragmentsReceived4XHorizontal.name: linkFragmentsReceived4XHorizontal
linkFragmentsReceived4XHorizontal.description: Engineering use only. Number of fragments received in 4x (256-QAM) modulation. For MIMO only. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

signalToNoiseRatioHorizontal.name: signalToNoiseRatioHorizontal
signalToNoiseRatioHorizontal.description: Estimate of the receive signal to noise ratio in dB. MIMO radios only. For MIMO this is the horizontal path.

linkSignalStrengthRatio.name: linkSignalStrengthRatio
linkSignalStrengthRatio.description: Signal Strength Ratio in dB is the power received by the vertical antenna input (dB) - power received by the horizontal antenna input (dB). MIMO radios only.

linkRadioDbmHorizontal.name: linkRadioDbmHorizontal
linkRadioDbmHorizontal.description: Receive power level of the horizontal antenna in dBm. MIMO radios only.

linkRadioDbmVertical.name: linkRadioDbmVertical
linkRadioDbmVertical.description: Receive power level of the vertical antenna in dBm. MIMO radios only.

maxSMTxPwr.name: maxSMTxPwr
maxSMTxPwr.description: Returns whether SM is transmitting at its configured max power level.

productType.name: productType
productType.description: Returns which type of product the SM is. PMP450 APs only.

linkAdaptRateLowPri.description: The current transmitting rate of the low priority VC. 0 : SM is not in session 1 : 1X QPSK SISO 2 : 2X 16-QAM SISO or QPSK MIMO 3 : 3X 64-QAM SISO 4 : 4X 256-QAM SISO or 16-QAM MIMO 6 : 6X 64-QAM MIMO 8 : 8X 256-QAM MIMO

linkAdaptRateHighPri.description: The current transmitting rate of the high priority VC. -1 : High Priority Channel not configured 0 : SM is not in session 1 : 1X QPSK SISO 2 : 2X 16-QAM SISO or QPSK MIMO 3 : 3X 64-QAM SISO 4 : 4X 256-QAM SISO or 16-QAM MIMO 6 : 6X 64-QAM MIMO 8 : 8X 256-QAM MIMO
